A taxi driver has been killed after he crashed into a tree in the Mfuleni area in Cape Town on Sunday. On arrival paramedics, found the man trapped inside the taxi. “The man had to be extricated with the jaws of life. And it was found that he was in a critical condition,” ER24 said. The man was later transported to Groote Schuur hospital for further medical care but shortly after arriving at the hospital, he was declared dead. The cause of the crash is still unknown. -TNA Reporter    